# Cairo Testing & Formatting Workflow

## Running Tests

Use `snforge test <test_prefix>` instead of `scarb test <test_prefix>` when running specific tests. `snforge test` matches tests whose name starts with the given prefix and is significantly faster.

```bash
# Good - fast, targeted
snforge test test_redeem_from_vault_with_mixed

# Avoid for specific tests - slower, compiles everything
scarb test test_redeem_from_vault_with_mixed
```

Use `scarb test` only when running the full test suite.

## Building

Run both dev and release builds to ensure compilation succeeds in both modes:

```bash
scarb build
scarb --release build
```

## Code Formatting

Always run `scarb fmt -w` after finishing code changes and before running tests. This ensures all code is properly formatted before review.

## Task Timing

When executing a plan with to-dos, track and report:
- Time taken to complete each individual to-do
- Total elapsed time for the entire task

Report these timings when summarizing completed work.
